The Minerals Resources Department is sending a a team to Kwahlathi to investigate whether residents have in fact discovered a massive trove of diamonds (eNCA/Screenshot) LADYSMITH - Mining experts have determined that stones found in KwaHlati in Ladysmith, KwaZulu-Natal are quartz crystals, not diamonds. The team made the announcement on Sunday. READ: Officials arrive in KwaHlathi to take samples of mystery stones People flocked to the area in the belief that the stones were diamonds. The team assigned to investigate the alleged discovery of diamonds in Kwazulu-Natal has released its findings. These indicate the stones are, in fact, quartz crystals. #DStv403 pic.twitter.com/F14NhOvQZB